The '''Emerald Coast Science Center (ECSC)''' is hands-on science discovery center located in [[Fort Walton Beach]], [[Okaloosa County, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Emerald Coast Science Center receives $13,000 grant|url=http://www.nwfdailynews.com/news/20161031/emerald-coast-science-center-receives-13000-grant|publisher=NFW Daily News|accessdate=29 June 2017|date=October 31, 2016}}</ref> 

The Center was established in 1989 as the FOCUS (Families of Okaloosa County Understanding Science) Center, and changed its name to Emerald Coast Science Center in 2001.<ref>{{cite web|title=About the Emerald Coast Science Center|url=http://www.ecscience.org/about|publisher=Emerald Coast Science Center|accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref> ECSC is a nonprofit center with a mission of inspiring and growing a scientifically engaged community.  

== Exhibits ==

Exhibits include both inside and outside spaces.  Inside the museum features an animal room, a Makerspace room, KITS in the kitchen, the Florida Ecosystem exhibit room and two main open floor plan halls that host hands-on exhibits, brain games, robotics exhibits and more.  The outside space hosts a turtle habitat, butterfly garden, shuffleboard court and more.  
<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nwfdailynews.com/news/20160716/animals-are-latest-focus-at-emerald-coast-science-center|title=Animals are the latest focus at the Emerald Coast Science Center|last=GALVAN|first=ABRAHAM|work=Northwest Florida Daily News|access-date=2017-07-29|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.visitflorida.com/en-us/listing.a0t40000007qsylAAA.html|title=Emerald Coast Science Center in Fort Walton Beach, FL{{!}} VISIT FLORIDA|website=Visit Florida|access-date=2017-07-29}}</ref> 

